# Keep docs in sync with every change

Any change to the repository (code, build, structure, behavior) **must** be reflected in:

| File / dir | Update when |
| --- | --- |
| `CHANGELOG.md` | Always — add an entry under the current unreleased/version section (Added / Changed / Removed / Fixed / Known issues). Source of truth. |
| `README.md` | Layout, build steps, usage, requirements, or links changed. |
| `docs/` | Behavior/feature/version changes mirrored into the relevant page (see below). |

## docs/ targets

- `docs/roadmap/roadmap-data.js` — backlog/version/task changes (also see `roadmap-backlog-sync.mdc`).
- `docs/release/<x.y.z>/release-data.js` — release-notes content for the current version.
- `docs/manual.txt` — usage/CLI/registry behavior changes.

## Rules

1. **No silent changes.** If you touch behavior, build, or structure, update `CHANGELOG.md` in the same change set.
2. **Versioning continues from upstream 2.24** — next is `2.25`, then `2.26`, … (no fork bump to 3.x).
3. **English only** across `README.md`, `CHANGELOG.md`, and `docs/`.
4. **Maintainer:** Tuyn Doan.
5. Before finishing, verify links and version numbers are consistent across all three.

## Quick checklist

- [ ] `CHANGELOG.md` entry added/updated.
- [ ] `README.md` updated if build/layout/usage/links changed.
- [ ] Matching `docs/` page (roadmap / release / manual) updated.
- [ ] Versions and links consistent everywhere; English only.
